The paper discusses justification logics, which are a type of modal logic. Modal logic is often studied in the subfield of logic (cs.LO), but the paper specifically discusses the application of justification logics in modeling the behavior of agents in distributed systems. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the subfields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). Additionally, the paper discusses the replacement of modal knowledge with justification logic, which could be relevant to the subfields of programming languages (cs.PL) and machine learning (cs.LG).
